    • Method Detail

      • execute

        java.lang.Object execute(java.lang.Object obj)
                         throws IllegalComponentArgumentException,
                                ComponentExecutionException
        This method has to implemented by every component. typically for every component we will need to create an abstract class which will implement this method which will call a new version of execute (enforced by that abstract class)with less generic parameters.
        Parameters:
        obj - the input for the component Object
        Returns:
        the output from the component.Object
        Throws:
        IllegalComponentArgumentException - this exception will be thrown when the component is expecting a different parameter type than is sent in the argument. since we had to keep this method generic this rule will be enforced by the abstract components implementing this interface IllegalComponentArgumentException
        ComponentExecutionException
        See Also:
        FolderImporterComponent
